title: For Sale/Trade:  Beautiful Old Remington 514
location: Toledo,  Oregon Coast, Oregon Coast, Oregon
postcontent:
This is an all original Remington 514 in .22 caliber. It is chambered for .22 Short, Long or Long Rifle. This one still has at least 95% of its bluing. The stock is a very nice Black Walnut. The metal is very nice with only tiny flaws but you have to look for them. The stock is in fantastic shape for its age with only very minor flaws in the clear coat finish. No major scratches, dings or dents anywhere. These are going for 275 on Gunbrokers and they are nowhere near this nice. I did see several in the 150-175 price range but most look like 9 miles of pounded dogs ass. This thing is an absolute tack driver if you do your part. By all original, I mean that it has never been drilled for a scope nor has the stock been fitted with sling swivels. I prefer cash on this one but I will consider trades. I will let it go for 195 cash or trade value. Trades considered are limited to firearms and ammo only. I am not interested in services, pottery, tools, car parts or your neighbors chickens. Ammo I am interested in is .17 HMR, .22 LR, 9mm, .40 cal, 10mm, 45 acp, 357 magnum and .357 Sig, 5.56 Nato/.223, 5.45x39, 7.62x39 and 7.62x39 and 7.62x51/.308. No other calibers interest me at this time. I am also interested in mags in 5.45x39, 5.56/..223, 7.62x39 and 7.62x51/.308. Cash or mags with ammo will get my attention before any other trades.
The drop down list to choose from doesnt give all choices, so if you dont know, this is a single shot bolt action with the safety on the back of the bolt. This is a fantastic beginners rifle since there is no live round in the chamber after firing the round. We all know what is like to have a beginner wave a firearm around after firing one or more rounds while another is chambered and the safety has not yet been engaged. Please do a little research and look at the condition of all the others out there. You will be very happy to see the condition of this particular rifle. Feel free to contact me by email or phone.
Mike REDACTED
